      "lesson title": "Human Override: Knowing When to Step In",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson explores why human judgement remains a critical part of any AI-assisted workflow, even as automation becomes more capable and widespread. You will learn to recognise the situations where relying solely on AI output can introduce risk, and how to identify the moments that call for a human to step in and take control. Through practical examples, the lesson helps you build confidence in questioning, reviewing, and overriding AI-generated decisions when the context demands it. By the end, you will have a clearer sense of your own role as an active participant in AI-assisted processes, rather than a passive observer. This is a beginner-friendly lesson designed to give you the knowledge and awareness to work alongside AI tools more responsibly and effectively.",
